{"serial": "63020", "department_serial": 59, "code": "SS3037", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Logic Design", "ch": "邏輯設計"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Ying-Tsen Lin"], "ch": ["林映岑"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "S4", "room": "807"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "太空科學與工程學系", "en": "Department of Space Science and Engineering"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 1, "selected": 27, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "1.了解邏輯設計的基本概念及原理，包含布爾代數、邏輯門及電路設計。\n2.熟悉數位電路的分析和設計技術，掌握組合邏輯和時序邏輯電路的工作原理。\n3.能夠使用現代的邏輯設計工具來實現基本邏輯電路，並解決實際設計問題。\n4.培養學生對進階數位設計主題的理解，為未來的計算機架構和電子工程學習打下基礎。", "en": "1.Understand the fundamental concepts and principles of logic design, including Boolean algebra, logic gates, and circuit design.\n2.Become proficient in analyzing and designing digital circuits, focusing on combinational and sequential logic.\n3.Develop the ability to utilize modern logic design tools to implement basic logic circuits and solve practical design problems.\n4.Prepare students for advanced digital design topics and provide a foundation for future studies in computer architecture and electronic engineering."}, "outline": {"ch": "介紹邏輯設計的基本概念，布爾代數的定律與邏輯運算。\n介紹基本邏輯閘 (AND, OR, NOT, NAND, NOR, XOR, XNOR) 及其應用於組合邏輯電路。\n設計加法器、編碼器、解碼器、選擇器等組合電路。\n使用卡諾圖 (Karnaugh Maps) 及代數方法進行邏輯簡化。\n介紹時序邏輯電路的基本概念，包括觸發器與寄存器。\n探討各種觸發器的類型及如何設計基本的時序邏輯電路。\n介紹可編程邏輯裝置（如FPGA）和硬體描述語言（如Verilog）。", "en": "Introduction to the basic concepts of logic design, laws of Boolean algebra, and logical operations.\nIntroduction to basic logic gates (AND, OR, NOT, NAND, NOR, XOR, XNOR) and their applications in combinational circuits.\nDesign of combinational circuits such as adders, encoders, decoders, and multiplexers.\nSimplification of Boolean functions using Karnaugh Maps and algebraic techniques.\nIntroduction to the basic concepts of sequential logic circuits, including flip-flops and registers.\nExplore different types of flip-flops and how to design basic sequential logic circuits.\nIntroduction to programmable logic devices (such as FPGA) and hardware description languages (such as Verilog)."}, "textbook": {"ch": "Charles Roth, Fundamentals of Logic Design 7th Edition, ISBN-10: 1133628478, ISBN-13: 978-1133628477", "en": "Charles Roth, Fundamentals of Logic Design 7th Edition, ISBN-10: 1133628478, ISBN-13: 978-1133628477"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "35", "en": "35"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n實習/實驗", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "Practical Training Lab"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "作業: 25％\n實驗: 40％\n期中考: 15％\n期末考: 20％", "en": "Homework: 25％\nLab: 40％\nMidtearm: 15％\nFinal: 20％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "星期一15:00-16:00", "en": "Mon 15:00-16:00"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "17+1", "en": "17+1"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "配合實驗專題實作與報告時間調整。", "en": "Adjustable depending on students' final project progress."}, "domain": {"ch": "太空酬載\n\n\n、\n\n\n基礎學科", "en": "太空酬載\n\n\n、\n\n\n基礎學科"}, "map": {"ch": [{"competencies": "太空科學知識的建立", "rating": "(1)非常低", "assesments": ["無"]}, {"competencies": "日地系統觀測技術的培養", "rating": "(2)低", "assesments": ["無"]}, {"competencies": "整合創新與獨立思考", "rating": "(5)非常高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "實作/實驗"]}, {"competencies": "資料分析能力的養成", "rating": "(4)高", "assesments": ["紙筆測驗/會考", "作業練習", "口頭報告/口試", "專題研究報告(書面)", "實作/實驗"]}, {"competencies": "數值模式的應用", "rating": "(3)普通", "assesments": ["無"]}], "en": [{"competencies": "Buildup of Space science knowledge", "rating": "(1)VeryLow", "assesments": ["No assessment"]}, {"competencies": "Cultivation of Solar-Terrestrial observation technology", "rating": "(2)Low", "assesments": ["No assessment"]}, {"competencies": "Integration of innovation and critical thinking", "rating": "(5)VeryHigh", "assesments": ["Test/Exam", "Assignments